   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>g. One of Christ's Followers Betraying Christ,</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Another Denying Him Three Times,</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>and the Rest, as Sheep, Being Scattered</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>One of Christ's followers, Judas, betrayed Christ Luke 22:21-23, 47-48 .</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Another of His followers, Peter, denied Him three times under Satan's sifting Luke 22:31-34, 54-62 .</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Eventually, the rest, as sheep, were scattered Matt 26:31 , and the Lord Jesus was left alone.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>h.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The Jews Collaborating with the Roman Government</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>to Sentence Christ to Death and Crucify Him</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The Jews collaborated with the Roman government to sentence Christ to death and crucify Him Luke 23:1-43 .</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>That certainly was something of the satanic chaos, but eventually the outcome of that chaos was something very good.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>3.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The Divine Economy</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>in Christ's Crucifixion, Resurrection,</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>and Ascension</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Now we need to see the divine economy in Christ's crucifixion, resurrection, and ascension.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>a. God Judging Christ on the Cross</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>for the Sin of the World</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>and for the Sin of the Believers,</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>and Christ Dying an All-inclusive Vicarious Death</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>A great part of God's economy was Christ's death on the cross.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>God judged Christ on the cross for the sin of the world and for the sin of the believers John 1:29; 1 Cor 15:3 .</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Christ died an all-inclusive vicarious death John 19:34; 12:24 .</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>b.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>The Women Followers of Christ</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Watching His Crucifixion</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>The women followers of Christ watched His crucifixion Matt 27:55-56 .</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>This indicates that in loving the Lord Jesus the sisters are stronger than the brothers and are ahead of the brothers.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Whereas Peter and the other disciples forsook the Lord, the women followed Him from Gethsemane and eventually watched His crucifixion.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>c.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>Joseph, One Expecting the Kingdom of God,</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>and the Women Followers of Christ</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>Burying Christ in an Excellent Way</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>Joseph, one expecting the kingdom of God, had a high position in society and was a hidden disciple.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>He and the women followers of Christ buried Christ in an excellent way Luke 23:50-56; Matt 27:57-61 .</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>Christ was not born in an excellent way, and He did not die in an excellent way.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>However, His burial was excellent and according to the highest standard.</S>
   </TEXT>
